🛠 Workflow Stages
1. 	Checkout & Setup Java
• 	Pull your repo and set up JDK.
• 	Build your Java app with Maven/Gradle.
2. 	Inject Metadata
• 	Add labels/annotations or environment variables.
• 	Use GitHub Actions  or  for metadata injection.
3. 	Download & Extract Package
• 	Download dependencies or artifacts.
• 	Extract and prepare them for deployment.
4. 	Handle Secrets (SPI, SMTP, etc.)
• 	Store sensitive values in GitHub Secrets.
• 	Pass them into Kubernetes  manifests.
5. 	Promote Application Image
• 	Build Docker image.
• 	Push to container registry (e.g., GitHub Container Registry or Docker Hub).
6. 	Setup kubectl
• 	Configure  with cluster credentials (often via GitHub Secrets).
• 	Install  and / if needed.
7. 	Delete StatefulSet (if required)
• 	Run  as part of cleanup.
8. 	Deploy to Kubernetes
• 	Apply manifests ().
• 	Or use Helm for templated deployments.
9. 	Post-Deployment Tasks
• 	Run smoke tests.
• 	Verify pods/services are healthy.
10. 	Complete Job
• 	Mark workflow success.
• 	Notify via Slack/email.
